Various python packaging tools (tested on OpenSuse, Centos 5/6)
===============================================================

build_rpm.sh - generate an rpm from pypi, or a source tarball
=============================================================

Allows you to package your applications without relying on 
site-packages to look sensible.

useage:
-------

build_rpm.sh package_name version python_version src_url


e.g. 
./build_rpm.sh requests 0.10.8 2.7

or

./build_rpm.sh python-memcached 1.48 2.7 http://ftp.tummy.com/pub/python-me  mcached/old-releases/python-memcached-1.48.tar.gz

notes:
------
Depends on: 
    py2pack
